abstract: Building on the message of the Occupy Wall Street movement, about 400 people brought their demonstration to some of the city's wealthiest residents.
snippet: Building on the message of the Occupy Wall Street movement, about 400 people brought their demonstration to some of the city's wealthiest residents.
lead_paragraph: Rupert Murdoch was not answering his front door. Neither was JPMorgan Chase's chief executive, Jamie Dimon. And when a crowd of eager guests showed up at the Park Avenue doorstep of the billionaire industrialist David H. Koch, instead of being greeted with open arms they were met by three stern men in suits, sunglasses and polished shoes.

headline.main: Upper East Side Protest March Makes House Calls
